[SN]TITLE[SN]
Two in hospital after Glasgow tenement fire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A fire in a block of tenement flats in Glasgow has left two people requiring hospital treatment.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The emergency services were called to Glenapp Road in the Pollokshields area of the city at about 11:50.
Two people were taken to Queen Elizabeth University Hospital. They are thought to have been suffering from smoke inhalation.
Other residents from the flats received medical assessments at the scene.
